This is a Quarto website. I am now realizing that doing the lab before the homework is due is very helpful because you get a basic understanding on how to make a quarto website which is what the HW asks you to do at the end to display your results!! If I did this assignment before I finished HW1, then I would have done HW1 at the speed of light!
The speed of light in a vacuum is \(C=\lambda f\) Speaking of light, how to estimate the value of dark matter using simulations is cited Perez et al. (2023).

title: My reveal.js format presentation
text:
Reference
If you ever want to learn more about astrophysical simulations, here I reference the paper that my internship last summer focused on (Perez et al. 2023).


Code
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

x = np.linspace(0, 50, 200)
y = np.sin(x)

plt.figure()
plt.plot(x, y)
plt.title("Sine Wave")
plt.xlabel("x")
plt.ylabel("sin(x)")
plt.show()







Perez, Lucia A., Shy Genel, Francisco Villaescusa-Navarro, Rachel S. Somerville, Austen Gabrielpillai, Daniel Anglés-Alcázar, Beth A. Wandelt, and L. Y. Aaron Yung. 2023. “Constraining Cosmology with Machine Learning and Galaxy Clustering: The CAMELS-SAM Suite.” The Astrophysical Journal 954 (1): 11. https://doi.org/10.3847/1538-4357/accd52.
